  "text": "The Apache Kafka broker validates SASL mechanism configuration at startup through a multi-layered validation chain:\n\n1. **Primary Configuration Definition and Validation** (BrokerSecurityConfigs.java, SaslConfigs.java):\n   - BrokerSecurityConfigs.java defines SASL_ENABLED_MECHANISMS_CONFIG with default value of [\"GSSAPI\"]\n   - SaslConfigs.java defines all mechanism-specific configurations and their documentation\n   - These files provide the configuration definitions used during broker initialization\n\n2. **Broker Startup Configuration Validation** (KafkaConfig.scala):\n   - KafkaConfig.validateValues() is called during broker initialization to validate all broker configurations\n   - The validateValues() method (lines 627-629) contains critical validation: it requires that the SASL_MECHANISM_INTER_BROKER_PROTOCOL_CONFIG must be included in SASL_ENABLED_MECHANISMS_CONFIG\n   - This validation occurs at broker startup time, ensuring proper mechanism configuration\n   - saslEnabledMechanisms() method retrieves the list of enabled mechanisms per listener\n   - validateWithMetadataVersion() provides additional validation after metadata version changes\n\n3. **SASL Channel Builder and JAAS Context Loading** (ChannelBuilders.java, JaasContext.java):\n   - ChannelBuilders.createSaslChannelBuilder() is invoked during server initialization\n   - For each mechanism in SASL_ENABLED_MECHANISMS_CONFIG, the code loads JAAS context via JaasContext.loadServerContext(listenerName, mechanism, configs)\n   - This is where JAAS config presence is checked - if JAAS_CONFIG is missing for an enabled mechanism, an exception is thrown\n   - Each mechanism (SCRAM, GSSAPI, PLAIN, OAUTHBEARER) is validated for its specific JAAS configuration\n\n4. **JAAS Configuration Parsing and Validation** (JaasConfig.java, JaasContext.java):\n   - JaasConfig constructor parses the SASL_JAAS_CONFIG string and validates:\n     - That a login module is specified (throws IllegalArgumentException if missing)\n     - That valid control flags (REQUIRED, REQUISITE, SUFFICIENT, OPTIONAL) are present\n   - JaasContext.loadServerContext() loads the appropriate JAAS configuration for each mechanism\n   - Invalid JAAS configurations result in exceptions during broker startup, preventing the broker from starting\n\n5. **Mechanism-Specific Validation**:\n   - ScramSaslServer.java validates SCRAM-specific credentials and configuration\n   - OAuthBearerSaslServer.java validates OAUTHBEARER JWT configuration (token endpoints, JWKS endpoints, expected audience, expected issuer)\n   - PlainSaslServer.java validates PLAIN mechanism configuration\n   - SaslServerAuthenticator.java loads the enabled mechanisms list and validates authentication requests against enabled mechanisms\n\n6. **Dynamic Configuration and Runtime Validation** (DynamicBrokerConfig.scala):\n   - Lists all dynamic SASL configs that can be reconfigured (SASL_ENABLED_MECHANISMS_CONFIG, SASL_JAAS_CONFIG, etc.)\n   - On configuration changes, LoginManager.closeAll() clears the SASL login cache to force re-validation\n   - MetadataVersionConfigValidator.java validates config changes against the current metadata version\n\n7. **Credential Management for Mechanisms** (ScramPublisher.scala):\n   - ScramPublisher.onMetadataUpdate() handles mechanism-specific credential updates\n   - Ensures mechanism-specific configurations are properly initialized during metadata updates\n\n**Validation Summary**:\nThe validation chain ensures:\n- sasl.enabled.mechanisms contains valid mechanism names\n- JAAS config is present for each enabled mechanism\n- JAAS config is properly formatted (valid login module, valid control flags)\n- Mechanism-specific configurations are validated (SCRAM credentials, GSSAPI keytabs, OAUTHBEARER tokens/endpoints)\n- Inter-broker SASL mechanism is in the enabled mechanisms list\n- All validations occur at broker startup time, preventing misconfiguration from causing runtime failures"
}

